<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-276-496  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 276 496.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  May 15 1989 v6 n19 p1(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Virtual net services offer flexibility, ease of use. (buyersguide)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Briere, Daniel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The three major long-distance carriers, ATandamp;T, MCI and US Sprint,offer virtual network services that are sophisticated, easy to useand comparatively economical.andP;  Users are relieved of the staffingand maintenance requirements of private networks, yet retaincontrol over their networks.andP;  By providing on-line access to thecarrier computer network data bases, users are able to configuretheir networks as needed.andP;  Switched access and other forms ofaccess allow a company's smaller sites to be tied into thecorporate network through a single carrier.andP;  Features to considerwhen purchasing virtual network service are account codes,authorization codes, call screening, forced on-net routing,internetwork calling, network intercept announcements, networkmanagement systems, public switched network overflow, speeddialing and switched 56K-bps.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Virtual Private NetworksSoftware SelectionTelecommunications.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>